Package: BLPlabtools
Title: Tools for meta-analysis and experimental data from the BLP Lab
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Seth Ariel", "Green", email = "setgree@stanford.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3909-1969")),
    person("John-Henry", "Pezzuto", email = "jdp2150@columbia.edu", role = c("aut"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5213-4201"))
    )
Author: Seth Ariel Green [aut, cre], John-Henry Pezzuto [aut]
Maintainer: Seth Ariel Green <setgree@stanford.edu>
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for meta-analysis and experimental data
    analysis developed by the BLP Lab. Provides functions for converting
    effect sizes from various statistical reports into standardized formats
    (Cohen's D, Glass's Delta), performing robust meta-analyses with clustered
    standard errors, creating publication-ready forest plots and tables, and
    ensuring computational reproducibility through Docker integration. Designed
    for social psychology research but broadly applicable to experimental and
    meta-analytic work.
